
Phase 1 — Install Debian

Phase 2 — Enable contrib/non-free repos

Edit:

  sudo nano /etc/apt/sources.list

  Make sure Debian 13 repos contain:

  main contrib non-free-firmware

UPDATES:

  sudo apt update && sudo apt full-upgrade -y

Reboot:
  sudo reboot

PHASE 3 — Install Build Tools

  sudo apt install -y build-essential git curl wget unzip cmake meson ninja-build pkg-config

PHASE 4 — Install Xorg

  sudo apt install xorg xorg-dev xinput xbacklight xdotool dbus-x11

PHASE 5 — Install i3

  sudo apt install i3 sxhkd

Verify:
  i3 --version
  sxhkd -v

PHASE 6 — Install UI Components
  sudo apt install polybar rofi dunst picom feh

PHASE 7 — File Manager

  sudo apt install thunar thunar-volman thunar-archive-plugin gvfs-backends

Phase 8 — Audio
sudo apt install -y \
pipewire-audio \
pamixer \
pulsemixer \
pavucontrol

Used by:

scripts/changevolume
Phase 9 — Power & Network
sudo apt install -y \
network-manager-gnome \
lxpolkit \
xfce4-power-manager \
acpi \
acpid

Enable:

sudo systemctl enable acpid
Phase 10 — Utilities
sudo apt install -y \
flameshot \
qimgv \
fd-find
Phase 11 — Fonts

The repo installs Nerd Fonts separately.

For your setup:

mkdir -p ~/.local/share/fonts

Download:

Nerd Fonts Releases

I'd recommend:

JetBrainsMono Nerd Font

or

CaskaydiaCove Nerd Font

Extract into:

~/.local/share/fonts/

Refresh:

fc-cache -fv
Phase 12 — Install Ghostty

Debian repos may not have the latest Ghostty.

Official docs:

Ghostty Documentation

Install Ghostty first before copying configs.

Verify:

ghostty

runs.

Phase 13 — Install Brave

Official:

Brave Linux Installation

After installation:

brave-browser
Phase 14 — Install Zsh
sudo apt install -y zsh

Set default shell:

chsh -s $(which zsh)

Log out and back in.

Phase 15 — Install Eza

Debian 13 should have:

sudo apt install -y eza

Verify:

eza --version
Phase 16 — Display Manager

The script installs LightDM.

I'd recommend:

sudo apt install -y lightdm lightdm-gtk-greeter

Enable:

sudo systemctl enable lightdm
Phase 17 — Copy Config Files

Create:

mkdir -p ~/.config

Copy from the repo:

i3/

to:

~/.config/i3/
Phase 18 — Make Scripts Executable
chmod +x ~/.config/i3/scripts/*
Phase 19 — Install GTK Themes & Icons

The repo expects:

Gruvbox
Nord
Catppuccin
Dracula
Everforest
Github Dark
TokyoNight

You can install them manually later.

For now:

sudo apt install -y nwg-look

which lets you switch GTK themes visually.

Phase 20 — Install Neovim From Source

Since you want latest Neovim:

git clone https://github.com/neovim/neovim.git
cd neovim
make CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release
sudo make install

Verify:

nvim --version
Phase 21 — Install Lazy.nvim

Official:

Lazy.nvim Installation Guide

Then install theme plugins:

gruvbox.nvim
nord.nvim
catppuccin
tokyonight.nvim
dracula.nvim
everforest
github-nvim-theme
Phase 22 — Your Theme System Modification

Modify every:

~/.config/i3/themes/*/theme.conf

Example:

name=Gruvbox

gtk=Gruvbox-Dark
icons=Gruvbox-Plus-Dark

ghostty=Gruvbox Dark

nvim=gruvbox

Then modify:

~/.config/i3/scripts/thememenu

to update Neovim as we discussed.

Phase 23 — First Start

From TTY:

startx

or reboot:

sudo reboot

At LightDM:

Session → i3

Login.

You should get:

i3
Polybar
Picom
Dunst
Rofi
Ghostty
Thunar

running.

Things I'd Remove From The Original Repo For Your Build

Based on our discussion:

Delete:
✓ workspaces.conf
✓ welcome notification block
✓ Firefox keybinds
✓ Geany keybinds
✓ st terminal references

Replace:
✓ Firefox → Brave
✓ st → Ghostty
✓ Geany → Neovim
✓ Bash → Zsh

That will give you a cleaner Debian 13 + i3 setup tailored to what you want while still keeping the structure and theme system from the original repository.
